snippet: Reports that more than 150,000 jobs have been created can be seen as good news for President Obama's re-election prospects.
abstract: Reports that more than 150,000 jobs have been created can be seen as good news for President Obama's re-election prospects.
lead_paragraph: 10:37 a.m. Friday | Updated On Friday morning, the Labor Department announced that the economy added 243,000 jobs in January and an average of 201,000 jobs over the last three months.

headline.main: Obama's Magic Number? 150,000 Jobs Per Month
